cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and text summarization. It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves selecting important concepts from a large amount of text. Additionally, the use of feature selection approaches and the na\""ive Bayes classifier suggest that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the focus on biomedical domain and the use of the Unified Medical Language System (UMLS) concepts could also make it relevant to cs.CY (Computers and Society).
